"offset":5004},"end":{"line":62,"column":383,"offset":5053}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":62,"column":1,"offset":4671},"end":{"line":62,"column":383,"offset":5053}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"CUE solves a number of pain points, such as dealing with white space in YAML or configuration templating. “If you ever find yourself fighting with white space in YAML,” Paul said, “that is an area that CUE can solve.” Essentially, CUE is trying to solve the problem of configurations at scale. Considering how often non-engineers are in charge of maintaining configuration, Paul explained, CUE is also designed to be approachable and accessible.","position":{"start":{"line":64,"column":1,"offset":5055},"end":{"line":64,"column":446,"offset":5500}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":64,"column":1,"offset":5055},"end":{"line":64,"column":446,"offset":5500}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The end result is the ability to have a “unified view of your configuration across many different systems, as opposed to different configurations and different tooling for different parts of whatever your system may be.”","position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1,"offset":5502},"end":{"line":66,"column":221,"offset":5722}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":66,"column":1,"offset":5502},"end":{"line":66,"column":221,"offset":5722}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"},{"type":"element","tagName":"h3","properties":{"id":"What-can-CUE-do","style":"position:relative;"},"children":[{"type":"element","tagName":"a","properties":{"href":"#What-can-CUE-do","aria-label":"What can CUE do permalink","class":"anchor before"},"children":[{"type":"raw","value":"<svg aria-hidden=\"true\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" viewBox=\"0 18 95 120\" height=\"18\" width=\"18\"><path d=\"M53.69,78.7H37.94l-5.85,25H21.74l5.85-25H15.89L18,69.1H29.84l4.65-19.65H23.39l2.1-